\fs36 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Malware(Malicious Software): An encompassing classification for harmful software scripts (viruses, trojans, worms) engineered to discrupt system architectures. Modern malware frequently uses polymorphic structures to alter its cryptographic signature and evade legacy antivirus systems.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Phishing: A prevalent form of social engineering where attackers masquerade as trusted entities over electronic communications. This remains the statistically dominant initial compromise vector globally for credential harvesting.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Ransomware: A severe threat variant that encrypts an organization\'92s primary storage systems, holding data access hostage until a cryptocurrency ransom is paid. Modern threat groups rely heavily on frameworks, where files are both encrypted locally and breaking both availability.}